  "intro": "Ahupuaʻa are traditional Hawaiian land divisions running mauka to makai — ridge to reef — so each holds a full watershed. This map overlays them on stream channels and basins computed from a USGS 10 m elevation model, so you can see where the old boundaries and the actual drainage agree, and where they part."
